    <p><strong>Perform the activities related to <em>Sorting Data, Number Formatting, and Chart Creation</em> as shown in the given table:</strong></p>

    <p><strong>Using the given table, complete the following steps:</strong></p>

    <ol>
      <li><strong>Sort the data:</strong><br>
        Sort the data by the <b>Salesperson</b> column in ascending (Aâ€“Z) order using the Custom Sort feature.<br>
        Select the entire data table and apply <b>All Borders</b>, then apply a <b>Thick Outside Border</b> to outline the table clearly.
      </li>

      <li><strong>Apply Number Formatting:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li><b>Total Revenue:</b> Currency</li>
          <li><b>Units Sold:</b> Number</li>
          <li><b>Order Date:</b> Short Date</li>
          <li><b>Transaction Time:</b> Time</li>
          <li><b>Discount Rate:</b> Percentage (with 1 decimal place)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>

      <li><strong>Create a Chart:</strong><br>
        Create a chart to compare the <b>Total Revenue</b> for each <b>Product Category</b>, and complete the following within the chart:
        <ol type="1">
          <li>Identify and indicate the Product Category with the highest Total Revenue.</li>
          <li>Add a clear title to the chart.</li>
          <li>Label the X-axis and Y-axis appropriately.</li>
          <li>Apply a pre-set Chart Style of your choice for better visual presentation.</li>
        </ol>
      </li>
    </ol>
